{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":989360,"duration_api_ms":946531,"num_turns":47,"result":"All 3 CR19 amendments implemented and verified. Results: 683 integration tests passed, 341 lib tests passed, clippy clean, fmt clean, new feature-gated test passes.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"change_summary\": \"Nineteenth remediation round addressing 3 amendments: (1) Added test snapshot_write_failure_during_backoff_routes_through_fail_run using a BackoffFailingSnapshotWriteStore that simulates a disk error specifically during the pre-backoff snapshot write. The test verifies the engine returns an error, the run ends in Failed state (not stranded in Running), the stage_failed journal event is present, and a run_failed journal event is emitted by fail_run_result. (2) CRITICAL: Fixed the bare `?` propagation on pre-backoff snapshot write that bypassed fail_run_result, leaving run.json stranded in Running state on disk failure. The error is now caught and routed through fail_run_result after restoring active_run from interrupted_run so fail_run's preserve_interrupted_run sees valid state. fail_run_result re-attempts the snapshot write (which succeeds because the snapshot now has a different status_summary) and emits a run_failed journal event, ensuring the run ends in a recoverable Failed state. (3) Fixed jitter same-tick correlation: added a thread-local monotonic counter (JITTER_COUNTER) that is XOR-mixed with subsec_nanos before the hash step. The counter increments on every call, guaranteeing distinct inputs even when multiple calls land within the same clock tick on coarse-clock platforms. Uses Knuth multiplicative hash (2654435761) for the counter mixing to spread bits before the murmur-style final mix.\",\n  \"outstanding_risks\": [\n    \"Process group kill cannot be implemented due to #![forbid(unsafe_code)] — pre_exec(setsid) requires unsafe, and std::process::Command::process_group is nightly-only. Grandchildren spawned by claude/codex CLI may survive as orphans after the parent is killed on timeout/cancel.\",\n    \"The pre-backoff snapshot write failure path restores active_run from interrupted_run before calling fail_run_result. If the snapshot write in fail_run also fails (truly broken disk), the error propagates with no recovery possible. This is acceptable — if the filesystem is completely broken, no code path can produce a valid on-disk snapshot.\",\n    \"The BackoffFailingSnapshotWriteStore test fixture triggers on status_summary.starts_with('retrying'), which is specific to the pre-backoff write path. If the status_summary format changes, the test will need updating. This coupling is intentional — the test targets exactly the pre-backoff write behavioral change.\",\n    \"The BinaryNotFound failure class name is used for both missing binaries and missing API keys. Doc comments clarify this dual use as a general 'fatal infrastructure prerequisite' signal.\",\n    \"The thread-local JITTER_COUNTER wraps at u32::MAX. After 4 billion jitter calls on the same thread, the counter repeats. This is far beyond any realistic retry scenario and has no practical impact.\",\n    \"The jitter implementation combines SystemTime subsec_nanos with the thread-local counter. Cross-thread calls at the same nanosecond with the same counter value would still produce identical jitter, but this requires two threads to have made exactly the same number of jitter calls — vanishingly unlikely in practice.\"\n  ],\n  \"steps\": [\n    {\n      \"description\": \"CRITICAL: Replaced bare `?` propagation on pre-backoff snapshot write (engine.rs:4649) with error handling that catches the write failure, restores active_run from interrupted_run (so fail_run's preserve_interrupted_run sees valid state), wraps the error as StageCommitFailed, and routes it through fail_run_result. This ensures the run ends in a recoverable Failed state with a run_failed journal event, instead of being stranded in Running state when the error bypasses fail_run_result.\",\n      \"order\": 1,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Fixed jitter same-tick correlation in retry_policy.rs: added a thread_local JITTER_COUNTER (Cell<u32>) that increments on every apply_jitter call. The counter is mixed with subsec_nanos via XOR with Knuth multiplicative hash (counter.wrapping_mul(2654435761)) before the murmur-style hash step. This guarantees distinct jitter values even when multiple calls land within the same clock tick on coarse-clock platforms (1ms/10ms resolution VMs).\",\n      \"order\": 2,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Added BackoffFailingSnapshotWriteStore test fixture in workflow_engine_test.rs that delegates to FsRunSnapshotWriteStore but returns an Io error when the snapshot status is Failed and status_summary starts with 'retrying' — targeting exactly the pre-backoff write path.\",\n      \"order\": 3,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Added integration test snapshot_write_failure_during_backoff_routes_through_fail_run: uses BackoffFailingSnapshotWriteStore with 1 transient implementation failure. Verifies: (a) engine returns error, (b) on-disk snapshot is in Failed state (not stranded in Running), (c) stage_failed journal event with will_retry=true is present, (d) run_failed journal event from fail_run_result is present.\",\n      \"order\": 4,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Ran cargo fmt to fix formatting differences in the new code, verified all checks pass: 683 integration tests, 341 lib tests, clippy clean, fmt clean. Feature-gated test snapshot_write_failure_during_backoff_routes_through_fail_run passes with --features test-stub.\",\n      \"order\": 5,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"validation_evidence\": [\n    \"cargo test --test unit: 683 passed, 0 failed, 0 ignored\",\n    \"cargo test --lib: 341 passed, 0 failed, 0 ignored\",\n    \"cargo clippy: no warnings or errors (Checking ralph-burning → Finished dev profile)\",\n    \"cargo fmt --check: no formatting differences (exit 0, no output)\",\n    \"snapshot_write_failure_during_backoff_routes_through_fail_run (--features test-stub): 1 transient implementation failure triggers backoff, BackoffFailingSnapshotWriteStore fails the pre-backoff write, engine catches error and routes through fail_run_result, on-disk snapshot ends in Failed state, stage_failed and run_failed journal events both present\",\n    \"Pre-backoff snapshot write failure path at engine.rs:4649-4680: if write fails, restores snapshot.active_run from interrupted_run.take(), resets status to Running, wraps as StageCommitFailed, routes through fail_run_result which re-attempts snapshot write (succeeds because snapshot is no longer in 'retrying' state) and emits run_failed journal event\",\n    \"apply_jitter now uses JITTER_COUNTER thread_local: each call increments counter and mixes it into the hash input via XOR with Knuth multiplicative hash, ensuring distinct jitter even when subsec_nanos is identical across calls on coarse-clock systems\",\n    \"Existing jitter tests (jitter_enabled_backoff_stays_within_expected_range, jitter_never_exceeds_backoff_cap) continue to pass — the counter mixing preserves the [0.75, 1.25) output range and post-jitter re-cap\",\n    \"All existing retry tests pass: retry_success_on_second_attempt (backoff round-trip), retry_exhaustion (5 attempts), cancellation_between_retry_attempts (InvocationCancelled), resume-from-failed tests (6 stage entries)\",\n    \"resume_state_tests unit tests pass: terminal_failure_clears_retry_tracking, resume_after_retryable_failure_preserves_attempt, resume_without_prior_failures_starts_at_attempt_1, completion_round_advance_resets_retry_tracking\"\n  ]\n}\n```","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"2ab56341-dc03-426c-ace5-dda05f3b0827","total_cost_usd":3.8660425,"usage":{"input_tokens":39,"cache_creation_input_tokens":135564,"cache_read_input_tokens":5001131,"output_tokens":14955,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":135564,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":41,"outputTokens":15224,"cacheReadInputTokens":5270725,"cacheCreationInputTokens":135980,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":3.8660425,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"f99f1a71-cd6e-4f9b-87e0-534e19dac2fd"}
